      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for microcode_ctl.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The microcode_ctl packages provide microcode updates for Intel and AMD processors.\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):\n\n* Update microcode_ctl to latest upstream [rhel-9.6.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-96929)\n\n* microcode_ctl: From CVEorg collector [rhel-9.6.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-91226)\n\n* microcode_ctl: From CVEorg collector [rhel-9.6.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-91233)\n\n* microcode_ctl: From CVEorg collector [rhel-9.6.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-91241)\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
